HEADWORD: Cirrostomi
<hw>Cir`ros"to*mi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. E. <ets>cirrus</ets> + Gr. <?/ mouth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The lowest group of vertebrates; -- so called from the cirri around
the mouth; the Leptocardia. See <er>Amphioxus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cirro-stratus</ent>⟦br⟧
